dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Rijm el-Kheil, sheet 47. Series G.S.G.S. no. 1522a
dct_description_sm: Shows Rujm el-Hiri monument. "Drawn and printed at the War Office, May 1917." Relief shown by form lines and by spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522a. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. Compiled for the Geographical Section, General Staff, War Office, by Lieut. Col. F.R. Maunsell, C.M.G. [from] 'Vom Mittelmeere zum Persischen Golf' by Max Freiherr von Oppenhim, 1893, Capt. T.C. Fowle I.A. Apil 1910." With glossary. Set complete, see index.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
